To compare the goodness of fit of our lab mixture VNIR reflectance spectra and the VNIR reflectance spectra acquired by orbiters and rovers, we employed a root mean square error calculation. For each observed spectrum Sobs, the original spectrum data Sobs, were retrieved and normalized at 800 nm. The observed normalization value Nobs, 800nm was obtained from the data at 800 nm. The normalized observed spectrum Sobs, norm was calculated by dividing the original observed spectrum by its normalization value:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
