				\begin{document}$${S}_{{obs},{norm}}=\frac{{S}_{{obs}}}{{N}_{{obs},800{nm}}}$$\end{document}Sobs,norm=SobsNobs,800nm

The root mean square error (RMSE) was then calculated by comparing the normalized observed spectrum Sobs, norm to the laboratory normalized spectrum Slab in the same way. This involved computing the differences ΔS between the two spectra, squaring these differences, averaging them, and finally taking the square root of the mean value:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
